{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":725,"text":"Like many of you, I'm one of the lucky people."},{"time":3836,"text":"I was born to a family where education was pervasive."},{"time":7236,"text":"I'm a third-generation PhD, a daughter of two academics."},{"time":11474,"text":"In my childhood, I played around in my father's university lab."},{"time":15268,"text":"So it was taken for granted that I attend some of the best universities,"},{"time":19117,"text":"which in turn opened the door to a world of opportunity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22918,"text":"Unfortunately, most of the people in the world are not so lucky."},{"time":27038,"text":"In some parts of the world, for example, South Africa,"},{"time":30173,"text":"education is just not readily accessible."},{"time":32878,"text":"In South Africa, the educational system was constructed"},{"time":35853,"text":"in the days of apartheid for the white minority."},{"time":38726,"text":"And as a consequence, today there is just not enough spots"},{"time":41426,"text":"for the many more people who want and deserve a high quality education."},{"time":45278,"text":"That scarcity led to a crisis in January of this year"},{"time":49158,"text":"at the University of Johannesburg."},{"time":50994,"text":"There were a handful of positions left open"},{"time":53125,"text":"from the standard admissions process, and the night before"},{"time":56094,"text":"they were supposed to open that for registration,"},{"time":58654,"text":"thousands of people lined up outside the gate in a line a mile long,"},{"time":62706,"text":"hoping to be first in line to get one of those positions."},{"time":66586,"text":"When the gates opened, there was a stampede,"},{"time":68894,"text":"and 20 people were injured and one woman died."},{"time":72546,"text":"She was a mother who gave her life"},{"time":74486,"text":"trying to get her son a chance at a better life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78549,"text":"But even in parts of the world like the United States"},{"time":81706,"text":"where education is available, it might not be within reach."},{"time":86062,"text":"There has been much discussed in the last few years"},{"time":88734,"text":"about the rising cost of health care."},{"time":90723,"text":"What might not be quite as obvious to people"},{"time":93365,"text":"is that during that same period the cost of higher education tuition"},{"time":97387,"text":"has been increasing at almost twice the rate,"},{"time":99867,"text":"for a total of 559 percent since 1985."},{"time":104147,"text":"This makes education unaffordable for many people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108681,"text":"Finally, even for those who do manage to get the higher education,"},{"time":112482,"text":"the doors of opportunity might not open."},{"time":115107,"text":"Only a little over half of recent college graduates"},{"time":118314,"text":"in the United States who get a higher education"},{"time":120627,"text":"actually are working in jobs that require that education."},{"time":124090,"text":"This, of course, is not true for the students"},{"time":125930,"text":"who graduate from the top institutions,"},{"time":127882,"text":"but for many others, they do not get the value"},{"time":130514,"text":"for their time and their effort."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134050,"text":"Tom Friedman, in his recent New York Times article,"},{"time":137080,"text":"captured, in the way that no one else could, the spirit behind our effort."},{"time":141448,"text":"He said the big breakthroughs are what happen"},{"time":144568,"text":"when what is suddenly possible meets what is desperately necessary."},{"time":148467,"text":"I've talked about what's desperately necessary."},{"time":151088,"text":"Let's talk about what's suddenly possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153600,"text":"What's suddenly possible was demonstrated by"},{"time":156719,"text":"three big Stanford classes,"},{"time":158287,"text":"each of which had an enrollment of 100,000 people or more."},{"time":162167,"text":"So to understand this, let's look at one of those classes,"},{"time":165551,"text":"the Machine Learning class offered by my colleague"},{"time":167471,"text":"and cofounder Andrew Ng."},{"time":169200,"text":"Andrew teaches one of the bigger Stanford classes."},{"time":171519,"text":"It's a Machine Learning class,"},{"time":172728,"text":"and it has 400 people enrolled every time it's offered."},{"time":176246,"text":"When Andrew taught the Machine Learning class to the general public,"},{"time":179511,"text":"it had 100,000 people registered."},{"time":182127,"text":"So to put that number in perspective,"},{"time":184136,"text":"for Andrew to reach that same size audience"},{"time":186495,"text":"by teaching a Stanford class,"},{"time":188321,"text":"he would have to do that for 250 years."},{"time":192247,"text":"Of course, he'd get really bored."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195733,"text":"So, having seen the impact of this,"},{"time":198470,"text":"Andrew and I decided that we needed to really try and scale this up,"},{"time":201598,"text":"to bring the best quality education to as many people as we could."},{"time":205718,"text":"So we formed Coursera,"},{"time":207213,"text":"whose goal is to take the best courses"},{"time":210350,"text":"from the best instructors at the best universities"},{"time":213667,"text":"and provide it to everyone around the world for free."},{"time":217695,"text":"We currently have 43 courses on the platform"},{"time":220295,"text":"from four universities across a range of disciplines,"},{"time":223494,"text":"and let me show you a little bit of an overview"},{"time":225327,"text":"of what that looks like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228605,"text":"(Video) Robert Ghrist: Welcome to Calculus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229818,"text":"Ezekiel Emanuel: Fifty million people are uninsured."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231698,"text":"Scott Page: Models help us design more effective institutions and policies."},{"time":234969,"text":"We get unbelievable segregation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237377,"text":"Scott Klemmer: So Bush imagined that in the future,"},{"time":239169,"text":"you'd wear a camera right in the center of your head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241547,"text":"Mitchell Duneier: Mills wants the student of sociology to develop the quality of mind ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245801,"text":"RG: Hanging cable takes on the form of a hyperbolic cosine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249466,"text":"Nick Parlante: For each pixel in the image, set the red to zero."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252537,"text":"Paul Offit: ... Vaccine allowed us to eliminate polio virus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255514,"text":"Dan Jurafsky: Does Lufthansa serve breakfast and San Jose? Well, that sounds funny."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259137,"text":"Daphne Koller: So this is which coin you pick, and this is the two tosses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262753,"text":"Andrew Ng: So in large-scale machine learning, we'd like to come up with computational ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266440,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":272049,"text":"DK: It turns out, maybe not surprisingly,"},{"time":274323,"text":"that students like getting the best content"},{"time":276561,"text":"from the best universities for free."},{"time":279448,"text":"Since we opened the website in February,"},{"time":281970,"text":"we now have 640,000 students from 190 countries."},{"time":286328,"text":"We have 1.5 million enrollments,"},{"time":288480,"text":"6 million quizzes in the 15 classes that have launched"},{"time":291330,"text":"so far have been submitted, and 14 million videos have been viewed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296246,"text":"But it's not just about the numbers,"},{"time":298764,"text":"it's also about the people."},{"time":300405,"text":"Whether it's Akash, who comes from a small town in India"},{"time":303381,"text":"and would never have access in this case"},{"time":305556,"text":"to a Stanford-quality course"},{"time":307045,"text":"and would never be able to afford it."},{"time":309560,"text":"Or Jenny, who is a single mother of two"},{"time":311598,"text":"and wants to hone her skills"},{"time":313565,"text":"so that she can go back and complete her master's degree."},{"time":316700,"text":"Or Ryan, who can't go to school,"},{"time":319836,"text":"because his immune deficient daughter"},{"time":321701,"text":"can't be risked to have germs come into the house,"},{"time":325084,"text":"so he couldn't leave the house."},{"time":326924,"text":"I'm really glad to say --"},{"time":328556,"text":"recently, we've been in correspondence with Ryan --"},{"time":330808,"text":"that this story had a happy ending."},{"time":332740,"text":"Baby Shannon -- you can see her on the left --"},{"time":334643,"text":"is doing much better now,"},{"time":335994,"text":"and Ryan got a job by taking some of our courses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340192,"text":"So what made these courses so different?"},{"time":342436,"text":"After all, online course content has been available for a while."},{"time":346156,"text":"What made it different was that this was real course experience."},{"time":349868,"text":"It started on a given day,"},{"time":351594,"text":"and then the students would watch videos on a weekly basis"},{"time":355228,"text":"and do homework assignments."},{"time":357083,"text":"And these would be real homework assignments"},{"time":358874,"text":"for a real grade, with a real deadline."},{"time":362178,"text":"You can see the deadlines and the usage graph."},{"time":364234,"text":"These are the spikes showing"},{"time":366322,"text":"that procrastination is global phenomenon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":370111,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":372687,"text":"At the end of the course,"},{"time":374359,"text":"the students got a certificate."},{"time":376215,"text":"They could present that certificate"},{"time":378375,"text":"to a prospective employer and get a better job,"},{"time":380528,"text":"and we know many students who did."},{"time":382588,"text":"Some students took their certificate"},{"time":384507,"text":"and presented this to an educational institution at which they were enrolled"},{"time":387629,"text":"for actual college credit."},{"time":389470,"text":"So these students were really getting something meaningful"},{"time":391684,"text":"for their investment of time and effort."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394518,"text":"Let's talk a little bit about some of the components"},{"time":397073,"text":"that go into these courses."},{"time":398965,"text":"The first component is that when you move away"},{"time":401593,"text":"from the constraints of a physical classroom"},{"time":403890,"text":"and design content explicitly for an online format,"},{"time":406730,"text":"you can break away from, for example,"},{"time":409258,"text":"the monolithic one-hour lecture."},{"time":411673,"text":"You can break up the material, for example,"},{"time":413458,"text":"into these short, modular units of eight to 12 minutes,"},{"time":416834,"text":"each of which represents a coherent concept."},{"time":419808,"text":"Students can traverse this material in different ways,"},{"time":422378,"text":"depending on their background, their skills or their interests."},{"time":426082,"text":"So, for example, some students might benefit"},{"time":428602,"text":"from a little bit of preparatory material"},{"time":431362,"text":"that other students might already have."},{"time":433433,"text":"Other students might be interested in a particular"},{"time":435873,"text":"enrichment topic that they want to pursue individually."},{"time":438959,"text":"So this format allows us to break away"},{"time":442194,"text":"from the one-size-fits-all model of education,"},{"time":445018,"text":"and allows students to follow a much more personalized curriculum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449010,"text":"Of course, we all know as educators"},{"time":451353,"text":"that students don't learn by sitting and passively watching videos."},{"time":454713,"text":"Perhaps one of the biggest components of this effort"},{"time":457658,"text":"is that we need to have students"},{"time":460250,"text":"who practice with the material"},{"time":462659,"text":"in order to really understand it."},{"time":465815,"text":"There's been a range of studies that demonstrate the importance of this."},{"time":469083,"text":"This one that appeared in Science last year, for example,"},{"time":471615,"text":"demonstrates that even simple retrieval practice,"},{"time":474447,"text":"where students are just supposed to repeat"},{"time":477239,"text":"what they already learned"},{"time":478639,"text":"gives considerably improved results"},{"time":480559,"text":"on various achievement tests down the line"},{"time":482828,"text":"than many other educational interventions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487132,"text":"We've tried to build in retrieval practice into the platform,"},{"time":490094,"text":"as well as other forms of practice in many ways."},{"time":492348,"text":"For example, even our videos are not just videos."},{"time":496492,"text":"Every few minutes, the video pauses"},{"time":498535,"text":"and the students get asked a question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500686,"text":"(Video) SP: ... These four things. Prospect theory, hyperbolic discounting,"},{"time":502907,"text":"status quo bias, base rate bias. They're all well documented."},{"time":505999,"text":"So they're all well documented deviations from rational behavior."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508766,"text":"DK: So here the video pauses,"},{"time":510390,"text":"and the student types in the answer into the box"},{"time":512646,"text":"and submits. Obviously they weren't paying attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":515884,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":516753,"text":"So they get to try again,"},{"time":518763,"text":"and this time they got it right."},{"time":521299,"text":"There's an optional explanation if they want."},{"time":523492,"text":"And now the video moves on to the next part of the lecture."},{"time":527749,"text":"This is a kind of simple question"},{"time":529627,"text":"that I as an instructor might ask in class,"},{"time":531708,"text":"but when I ask that kind of a question in class,"},{"time":534208,"text":"80 percent of the students"},{"time":535508,"text":"are still scribbling the last thing I said,"},{"time":537374,"text":"15 percent are zoned out on Facebook,"},{"time":540695,"text":"and then there's the smarty pants in the front row"},{"time":543151,"text":"who blurts out the answer"},{"time":544510,"text":"before anyone else has had a chance to think about it,"},{"time":546717,"text":"and I as the instructor am terribly gratified"},{"time":549589,"text":"that somebody actually knew the answer."},{"time":551237,"text":"And so the lecture moves on before, really,"},{"time":554029,"text":"most of the students have even noticed that a question had been asked."},{"time":557558,"text":"Here, every single student"},{"time":560165,"text":"has to engage with the material."}]},{"cues":[{"time":562949,"text":"And of course these simple retrieval questions"},{"time":564885,"text":"are not the end of the story."},{"time":566547,"text":"One needs to build in much more meaningful practice questions,"},{"time":569517,"text":"and one also needs to provide the students with feedback"},{"time":571870,"text":"on those questions."},{"time":573533,"text":"Now, how do you grade the work of 100,000 students"},{"time":576421,"text":"if you do not have 10,000 TAs?"},{"time":579503,"text":"The answer is, you need to use technology"},{"time":581857,"text":"to do it for you."},{"time":583352,"text":"Now, fortunately, technology has come a long way,"},{"time":586000,"text":"and we can now grade a range of interesting types of homework."},{"time":589268,"text":"In addition to multiple choice"},{"time":590795,"text":"and the kinds of short answer questions that you saw in the video,"},{"time":593948,"text":"we can also grade math, mathematical expressions"},{"time":597208,"text":"as well as mathematical derivations."},{"time":599160,"text":"We can grade models, whether it's"},{"time":602034,"text":"financial models in a business class"},{"time":604210,"text":"or physical models in a science or engineering class"},{"time":607194,"text":"and we can grade some pretty sophisticated programming assignments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610938,"text":"Let me show you one that's actually pretty simple"},{"time":612857,"text":"but fairly visual."},{"time":614337,"text":"This is from Stanford's Computer Science 101 class,"},{"time":616814,"text":"and the students are supposed to color-correct"},{"time":618418,"text":"that blurry red image."},{"time":620010,"text":"They're typing their program into the browser,"},{"time":622028,"text":"and you can see they didn't get it quite right, Lady Liberty is still seasick."},{"time":626086,"text":"And so, the student tries again, and now they got it right, and they're told that,"},{"time":629842,"text":"and they can move on to the next assignment."},{"time":632201,"text":"This ability to interact actively with the material"},{"time":635349,"text":"and be told when you're right or wrong"},{"time":637033,"text":"is really essential to student learning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640159,"text":"Now, of course we cannot yet grade"},{"time":642434,"text":"the range of work that one needs for all courses."},{"time":645268,"text":"Specifically, what's lacking is the kind of critical thinking work"},{"time":648569,"text":"that is so essential in such disciplines"},{"time":650491,"text":"as the humanities, the social sciences, business and others."},{"time":654088,"text":"So we tried to convince, for example,"},{"time":656337,"text":"some of our humanities faculty"},{"time":657953,"text":"that multiple choice was not such a bad strategy."},{"time":660649,"text":"That didn't go over really well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662840,"text":"So we had to come up with a different solution."},{"time":665273,"text":"And the solution we ended up using is peer grading."},{"time":668347,"text":"It turns out that previous studies show,"},{"time":670769,"text":"like this one by Saddler and Good,"},{"time":672441,"text":"that peer grading is a surprisingly effective strategy"},{"time":674929,"text":"for providing reproducible grades."},{"time":678143,"text":"It was tried only in small classes,"},{"time":679913,"text":"but there it showed, for example,"},{"time":681400,"text":"that these student-assigned grades on the y-axis"},{"time":683882,"text":"are actually very well correlated"},{"time":685193,"text":"with the teacher-assigned grade on the x-axis."},{"time":687489,"text":"What's even more surprising is that self-grades,"},{"time":690649,"text":"where the students grade their own work critically --"},{"time":692960,"text":"so long as you incentivize them properly"},{"time":694697,"text":"so they can't give themselves a perfect score --"},{"time":696635,"text":"are actually even better correlated with the teacher grades."},{"time":699826,"text":"And so this is an effective strategy"},{"time":701433,"text":"that can be used for grading at scale,"},{"time":703537,"text":"and is also a useful learning strategy for the students,"},{"time":706273,"text":"because they actually learn from the experience."},{"time":708528,"text":"So we now have the largest peer-grading pipeline ever devised,"},{"time":713177,"text":"where tens of thousands of students"},{"time":715681,"text":"are grading each other's work,"},{"time":716879,"text":"and quite successfully, I have to say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719948,"text":"But this is not just about students"},{"time":722208,"text":"sitting alone in their living room working through problems."},{"time":725249,"text":"Around each one of our courses,"},{"time":727056,"text":"a community of students had formed,"},{"time":729216,"text":"a global community of people"},{"time":731096,"text":"around a shared intellectual endeavor."},{"time":733628,"text":"What you see here is a self-generated map"},{"time":736280,"text":"from students in our Princeton Sociology 101 course,"},{"time":739241,"text":"where they have put themselves on a world map,"},{"time":742000,"text":"and you can really see the global reach of this kind of effort."}]},{"cues":[{"time":744960,"text":"Students collaborated in these courses in a variety of different ways."},{"time":749527,"text":"First of all, there was a question and answer forum,"},{"time":752166,"text":"where students would pose questions,"},{"time":754310,"text":"and other students would answer those questions."},{"time":756734,"text":"And the really amazing thing is,"},{"time":758447,"text":"because there were so many students,"},{"time":760117,"text":"it means that even if a student posed a question"},{"time":762482,"text":"at 3 o'clock in the morning,"},{"time":764114,"text":"somewhere around the world,"},{"time":765696,"text":"there would be somebody who was awake"},{"time":767770,"text":"and working on the same problem."},{"time":770083,"text":"And so, in many of our courses,"},{"time":772041,"text":"the median response time for a question"},{"time":774370,"text":"on the question and answer forum was 22 minutes."},{"time":777788,"text":"Which is not a level of service I have ever offered to my Stanford students."}]},{"cues":[{"time":782365,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":783706,"text":"And you can see from the student testimonials"},{"time":785648,"text":"that students actually find"},{"time":787335,"text":"that because of this large online community,"},{"time":789856,"text":"they got to interact with each other in many ways"},{"time":792455,"text":"that were deeper than they did in the context of the physical classroom."},{"time":796648,"text":"Students also self-assembled,"},{"time":798992,"text":"without any kind of intervention from us,"},{"time":800855,"text":"into small study groups."},{"time":802758,"text":"Some of these were physical study groups"},{"time":805120,"text":"along geographical constraints"},{"time":806946,"text":"and met on a weekly basis to work through problem sets."},{"time":809668,"text":"This is the San Francisco study group,"},{"time":811568,"text":"but there were ones all over the world."},{"time":813887,"text":"Others were virtual study groups,"},{"time":815919,"text":"sometimes along language lines or along cultural lines,"},{"time":818908,"text":"and on the bottom left there,"},{"time":820352,"text":"you see our multicultural universal study group"},{"time":824148,"text":"where people explicitly wanted to connect"},{"time":825911,"text":"with people from other cultures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":828917,"text":"There are some tremendous opportunities"},{"time":831028,"text":"to be had from this kind of framework."},{"time":834353,"text":"The first is that it has the potential of giving us"},{"time":838007,"text":"a completely unprecedented look"},{"time":840441,"text":"into understanding human learning."},{"time":842730,"text":"Because the data that we can collect here is unique."},{"time":846193,"text":"You can collect every click, every homework submission,"},{"time":850202,"text":"every forum post from tens of thousands of students."},{"time":854565,"text":"So you can turn the study of human learning"},{"time":856908,"text":"from the hypothesis-driven mode"},{"time":858841,"text":"to the data-driven mode, a transformation that,"},{"time":861699,"text":"for example, has revolutionized biology."},{"time":864740,"text":"You can use these data to understand fundamental questions"},{"time":868164,"text":"like, what are good learning strategies"},{"time":870044,"text":"that are effective versus ones that are not?"},{"time":872740,"text":"And in the context of particular courses,"},{"time":874980,"text":"you can ask questions"},{"time":876517,"text":"like, what are some of the misconceptions that are more common"},{"time":879772,"text":"and how do we help students fix them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":881949,"text":"So here's an example of that,"},{"time":883373,"text":"also from Andrew's Machine Learning class."},{"time":885389,"text":"This is a distribution of wrong answers"},{"time":887597,"text":"to one of Andrew's assignments."},{"time":889207,"text":"The answers happen to be pairs of numbers,"},{"time":891100,"text":"so you can draw them on this two-dimensional plot."},{"time":893371,"text":"Each of the little crosses that you see is a different wrong answer."},{"time":897149,"text":"The big cross at the top left"},{"time":899555,"text":"is where 2,000 students"},{"time":901703,"text":"gave the exact same wrong answer."},{"time":904748,"text":"Now, if two students in a class of 100"},{"time":907075,"text":"give the same wrong answer,"},{"time":908362,"text":"you would never notice."},{"time":909713,"text":"But when 2,000 students give the same wrong answer,"},{"time":912273,"text":"it's kind of hard to miss."},{"time":913970,"text":"So Andrew and his students went in,"},{"time":916162,"text":"looked at some of those assignments,"},{"time":917682,"text":"understood the root cause of the misconception,"},{"time":921770,"text":"and then they produced a targeted error message"},{"time":924290,"text":"that would be provided to every student"},{"time":926539,"text":"whose answer fell into that bucket,"},{"time":928718,"text":"which means that students who made that same mistake"},{"time":930802,"text":"would now get personalized feedback"},{"time":932828,"text":"telling them how to fix their misconception much more effectively."}]},{"cues":[{"time":937227,"text":"So this personalization is something that one can then build"},{"time":941038,"text":"by having the virtue of large numbers."},{"time":944178,"text":"Personalization is perhaps"},{"time":946490,"text":"one of the biggest opportunities here as well,"},{"time":948913,"text":"because it provides us with the potential"},{"time":951258,"text":"of solving a 30-year-old problem."},{"time":953948,"text":"Educational researcher Benjamin Bloom, in 1984,"},{"time":957297,"text":"posed what's called the 2 sigma problem,"},{"time":959548,"text":"which he observed by studying three populations."},{"time":962610,"text":"The first is the population that studied in a lecture-based classroom."},{"time":966218,"text":"The second is a population of students that studied"},{"time":968995,"text":"using a standard lecture-based classroom,"},{"time":970714,"text":"but with a mastery-based approach,"},{"time":972794,"text":"so the students couldn't move on to the next topic"},{"time":974714,"text":"before demonstrating mastery of the previous one."},{"time":978068,"text":"And finally, there was a population of students"},{"time":980362,"text":"that were taught in a one-on-one instruction using a tutor."},{"time":984890,"text":"The mastery-based population was a full standard deviation,"},{"time":988162,"text":"or sigma, in achievement scores better"},{"time":990450,"text":"than the standard lecture-based class,"},{"time":992844,"text":"and the individual tutoring gives you 2 sigma"},{"time":994988,"text":"improvement in performance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":996818,"text":"To understand what that means,"},{"time":998281,"text":"let's look at the lecture-based classroom,"},{"time":1000114,"text":"and let's pick the median performance as a threshold."},{"time":1003033,"text":"So in a lecture-based class,"},{"time":1004371,"text":"half the students are above that level and half are below."},{"time":1008250,"text":"In the individual tutoring instruction,"},{"time":1010348,"text":"98 percent of the students are going to be above that threshold."},{"time":1015149,"text":"Imagine if we could teach so that 98 percent of our students"},{"time":1019069,"text":"would be above average."},{"time":1021267,"text":"Hence, the 2 sigma problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1024690,"text":"Because we cannot afford, as a society,"},{"time":1027089,"text":"to provide every student with an individual human tutor."},{"time":1030161,"text":"But maybe we can afford to provide each student"},{"time":1032410,"text":"with a computer or a smartphone."},{"time":1034429,"text":"So the question is, how can we use technology"},{"time":1036618,"text":"to push from the left side of the graph, from the blue curve,"},{"time":1039993,"text":"to the right side with the green curve?"},{"time":1042731,"text":"Mastery is easy to achieve using a computer,"},{"time":1045068,"text":"because a computer doesn't get tired"},{"time":1046473,"text":"of showing you the same video five times."},{"time":1049546,"text":"And it doesn't even get tired of grading the same work multiple times,"},{"time":1052802,"text":"we've seen that in many of the examples that I've shown you."},{"time":1055828,"text":"And even personalization"},{"time":1057682,"text":"is something that we're starting to see the beginnings of,"},{"time":1059818,"text":"whether it's via the personalized trajectory through the curriculum"},{"time":1063010,"text":"or some of the personalized feedback that we've shown you."},{"time":1066274,"text":"So the goal here is to try and push,"},{"time":1068762,"text":"and see how far we can get towards the green curve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1072259,"text":"So, if this is so great, are universities now obsolete?"},{"time":1077618,"text":"Well, Mark Twain certainly thought so."},{"time":1080610,"text":"He said that, \"College is a place where a professor's lecture notes"},{"time":1083155,"text":"go straight to the students' lecture notes,"},{"time":1084858,"text":"without passing through the brains of either.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1087234,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1091281,"text":"I beg to differ with Mark Twain, though."},{"time":1093949,"text":"I think what he was complaining about is not"},{"time":1096614,"text":"universities but rather the lecture-based format"},{"time":1099364,"text":"that so many universities spend so much time on."},{"time":1102148,"text":"So let's go back even further, to Plutarch,"},{"time":1105307,"text":"who said that, \"The mind is not a vessel that needs filling,"},{"time":1107534,"text":"but wood that needs igniting.\""},{"time":1109557,"text":"And maybe we should spend less time at universities"},{"time":1111747,"text":"filling our students' minds with content"},{"time":1114318,"text":"by lecturing at them, and more time igniting their creativity,"},{"time":1118118,"text":"their imagination and their problem-solving skills"},{"time":1121373,"text":"by actually talking with them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1123871,"text":"So how do we do that?"},{"time":1125238,"text":"We do that by doing active learning in the classroom."},{"time":1128669,"text":"So there's been many studies, including this one,"},{"time":1131118,"text":"that show that if you use active learning,"},{"time":1133198,"text":"interacting with your students in the classroom,"},{"time":1135614,"text":"performance improves on every single metric --"},{"time":1138310,"text":"on attendance, on engagement and on learning"},{"time":1140759,"text":"as measured by a standardized test."},{"time":1142814,"text":"You can see, for example, that the achievement score"},{"time":1144678,"text":"almost doubles in this particular experiment."},{"time":1147548,"text":"So maybe this is how we should spend our time at universities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1151949,"text":"So to summarize, if we could offer a top quality education"},{"time":1156526,"text":"to everyone around the world for free,"},{"time":1158429,"text":"what would that do? Three things."},{"time":1161250,"text":"First it would establish education as a fundamental human right,"},{"time":1164671,"text":"where anyone around the world"},{"time":1166037,"text":"with the ability and the motivation"},{"time":1167958,"text":"could get the skills that they need"},{"time":1169909,"text":"to make a better life for themselves,"},{"time":1171494,"text":"their families and their communities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1173511,"text":"Second, it would enable lifelong learning."},{"time":1176142,"text":"It's a shame that for so many people,"},{"time":1178093,"text":"learning stops when we finish high school or when we finish college."},{"time":1181405,"text":"By having this amazing content be available,"},{"time":1183886,"text":"we would be able to learn something new"},{"time":1186629,"text":"every time we wanted,"},{"time":1187765,"text":"whether it's just to expand our minds"},{"time":1189094,"text":"or it's to change our lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1191053,"text":"And finally, this would enable a wave of innovation,"},{"time":1194198,"text":"because amazing talent can be found anywhere."},{"time":1197270,"text":"Maybe the next Albert Einstein or the next Steve Jobs"},{"time":1200278,"text":"is living somewhere in a remote village in Africa."},{"time":1202893,"text":"And if we could offer that person an education,"},{"time":1205549,"text":"they would be able to come up with the next big idea"},{"time":1207905,"text":"and make the world a better place for all of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1210309,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1211469,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}